    "heated debate about whether or not it should be allowed for academic writing [13].GenAI describes a subset of AI that is capable of creating new content.",
    "Although there are many forms of AI generated content (e.g.",
    "audio, video and images), I focus here on text generation that can pass as human-generated by large language models (LLMs), which is a form of GenAI.",
    "Among the largest GenAI models, there are some key players such as OpenAI's GPT series, Google's GEMINI, Meta AI's Llama and Anthropic's Claude [5].",
    "While each model differs in strength, price and performance, all are based on the same Transformer model architecture published by Vaswani et al. [29].The use of GenAI raises several ethical concerns, such as bias in the training data, creation of harmful content, large energy consumption, intellectual property and inequity of access [8,9]."
